        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 4 at 12:17PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 1217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Craig, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Craig, Hayden, Great Divide, Lay, Hamilton, Slater, Juniper Springs,
and Fortification.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 40 in Colorado between mile markers 64 and 117.
Colorado 13 between mile markers 64 and 127.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
